# CVE-2026-0287 — PAN-OS: Denial of Service Vulnerabilities in Network
# Traffic Processing.
# The advisory [2] describes specially crafted network traffic sent to
# PAN-OS dataplane interfaces causing DoS. No specific protocol, packet
# field, or payload pattern has been publicly disclosed (exploit maturity
# is UNREPORTED [2]). The threshold below is a heuristic intended to flag
# high-rate anomalous traffic toward common PAN-OS management/dataplane
# ports — this is a behavioural approximation ONLY and carries a high
# false-positive risk. It MUST be validated and tuned by an analyst
# familiar with the protected environment before any enforcement action
# is taken. Do NOT promote to drop/reject without PCAP-verified
# signatures.
#
# DRAFT — FOR ANALYST REVIEW ONLY.

alert ip $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET any (
  msg:"THREATFORGE CVE-2026-0287 PAN-OS dataplane DoS anomalous traffic volume";
  flow:stateless;
  threshold:type both, track by_src, count 1000, seconds 5;
  reference:cve,2026-0287;
